  ## 1.3 Reasoning System Architectures
  ### Static Reasoning
  System/Logic already configured
  Examples:
  - Logic Programmes
  - Deductive Classifier
  - Rule based Systems
  - Fuzzy Systems
  - Case-based reasoning systems
      - Similarity between cases
  
  ### Dynamic Reasoning
  Examples:
  - Search systems
  - Simulation systems
  - Optimisation systems
  - Recommendation systems
  - Knowledge Discovery (Data Mining, Machine Learning)
  - Hybrid Systems
  
  ### Cognitive Reasoning
  'cognition' involves some aspect of human-level context understanding
  
  Examples:
  - Semantic systems
  - Natural Language systems
  - Question Answering systems
  - Negotiation & Debate systems
  - Multi agent systems (swarm intelligence)
  - chat-bot system
  
  ### Proactive Reasoning Systems (Goal Driven)
  Examples:
  - Autonomous software system (sales chatbot, RPA)
  - Multi Agent cooperative system (warehouse robotic swarm)
  - constrain solver (global travel planner)
  
  
  ### Reactive Reasoning  Systems (Data Driven)
  Examples:
  - Business Rule Management System (BRMS)
  - Business Process Management System (BPMS)
  - Constrain Solver (Delivery vehicles scheduler)
  
  ### Goal Driven Systems
  Basically sequences of instructions based on backward chaining inference
  
  ### Data/Fact/Knowledge/Process/Rule-driven Systems
  - Basically seqeuences of instructions based on forward chaining inference
  - Data, Rules etc. stored in a knowledge base, system checks knowledge/rules and maps corresponding action
      - So like a system based entirely on if/else clauses
      - Except that the rules are stored in a repository
      - The program polls the repository for valid actions
      - The rules are not embedded inside the code
  
  
